It is sufficiently arduous for an upright client

To serve one earthly master, so it is difficult

To minister to many gods in a way that pleases them allÍ¾ For poor man is always reckoned less than the godheadl Since he often entreats the godhead's aid with bowed head. Thus any man who foolishly seeks many gods for himself Raves, since that which is impaired by a sum

In excess of all measure is rarely honorable,

Especially if a great and pressing matter expels measure And odious superfluity avoids what is sufficient.

A depraved people for whom one God is not enough wants To be pressed by its burden to the point of grave suffering5 So it is reasonable for those who live their lives sensibly To make their prayer to one God without equal,

That every man on earth might disdain the gods

And ridicule them to his own salvation.

For you there must be a single God, three and one,

Who is father, son, and fostering spirit:

God in his supreme godhead, but in such a way

That no knowing man perceives there are three gods:

Only the salvation and holy saving faith of Christians Grants eternal rest: it is sufficient

To consolidate the throne of salvation for its followers And give life adorned in radiance, dispelling light's end.
